The messaging system screws over average looking guys and girls, as well as members of the LGBTQ community. Why bother even writing a message if the person isn't going to see it? What's even better is the logic used by OkCupid staff to defend this junk. If someone was harassing or abusing you, the block and report buttons were always there for you. Too many messages? They weren't going away and you could get to them eventually. You could even delete and filter these messages out yourself too (pretty easy to go over and delete one word messages anyway). All of the reasons the staff are giving to defend this do not hold water. There is a pink X, but just to indicate you passed on the profile, you can't remove it, so the lots gets super cluttered. This is really bad UX, I messaged them about it and hope it will be changed. With some easy improvements, this would be a 4 or 5 star experience.

This app has great potential with its compatibility rating system, but infuriating design decisions and a critical bug make the app not worth using. If you do not like surprise video ads that appear after messages and swipes and PLAY WITH VOLUME ON BY DEFAULT, then avoid this app. It is effectively an unwritten UX standard now that if videos autoplay, then they must be muted by default, and it is truly baffling if blaring autoplaying ads through the user's speakers was an intentional design decision. Tinder, by contrast, does not show these kinds of ads. Another issue is a bug that has lingered for months now. In Double-Take (the swipe system), you can encounter people you have already rejected, which is a nice feature in the case that you change your mind or the person posts different pictures later. However, the current behavior is that Double-Take frequently shows you the same group of ten-or-so profiles IMMEDIATELY again (sometimes three, even four times total), including the profiles you liked and/or messaged. As soon as I start to see profiles I encountered 60 seconds ago, I close the app. I made my decisions. The only redeeming quality of the app is the compatibility rating system, which calculates and shows the percent compatibility you have with any other profile, based on your answers to questions.
